{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"coaching":[{"coaching":"Plan how acceptance criteria completeness and testability will be verified in-session — restate any deferred or unobservable success target as an observable proxy.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f607dd457c67f9209"],"move_id":"9","move_name":"plan the verification","subject":"acceptance criteria completeness and testability"},{"coaching":"Pin down legacy projection helper calling contract across stories with a concrete worked example.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f692eeca47a20c8eb"],"move_id":"6","move_name":"specification by example","subject":"legacy projection helper calling contract across stories"},{"coaching":"Record an ADR for operator compaction pause precondition on full downgrade — it reads like a one-way door.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f40ee0cbdefeff7ad"],"move_id":"8","move_name":"ADR / one-way-door","subject":"operator compaction pause precondition on full downgrade"},{"coaching":"Weigh at least one structural alternative for writer-disable mechanism without a configuration switch.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f4e468bad1817acd4"],"move_id":"5","move_name":"weigh alternatives","subject":"writer-disable mechanism without a configuration switch"},{"coaching":"Propagate the revision for schema output regression guard gaps in child stories to the child tickets.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f32a7625b9f5a38bf"],"move_id":"11","move_name":"propagate to children","subject":"schema output regression guard gaps in child stories"}],"coverage":{"counts":{"advisory_overflow":0,"advisory_surfaced":4,"blocking":0,"dropped":8,"indeterminate":0},"det":{"P1":{"ac_items":11,"blocking":false,"clarity_score":7,"name":"readiness-shape","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P2":{"blocking":false,"name":"resolution","ran":true,"references":0,"resolved":0,"status":"pass"},"P3":{"blocking":false,"name":"package-existence","packages":0,"ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P4":{"ac_items":11,"blocking":false,"desc_chars":11599,"file_impact":8,"name":"oversize","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P5":{"blocking":false,"children":3,"edges":3,"name":"task-dag","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P6":{"ac_items":11,"blocking":false,"name":"ac-quality","ran":true,"status":"fail","verify_commands_linted":4,"verify_lint_abstained":4},"P7":{"blocking":false,"destructive_hits":[],"name":"destructive-sniff","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P8":{"blocking":false,"budget_tokens":868000,"name":"reviewability","plan_tokens":2916,"ran":true,"status":"pass","worst_parent_child_pair_tokens":4786},"P9":{"applicable":false,"blocking":false,"file_impact":8,"name":"file-impact-coverage","ran":true,"status":"pass"}},"floored_criteria":["G4","T4"],"floored_finding_ids":["f692eeca47a20c8eb","f4e468bad1817acd4"],"llm_ran":true,"metrics":{"claim_path":"no-llm/no-network (structural; the fast claim check is a local HMAC verify)","det_ms":257.5,"llm_calls":23,"llm_ms":728350.2,"total_ms":728741.6,"verify_requests":34},"narrowed":true,"remediation":{"baseline":"signature","eligible":true,"reasons":{"code_unchanged":true,"plan_changed":true,"prior_sidecar":true,"registry_unchanged":true,"signed":true,"within_window":true}},"routing":{"agent_tier":["G3","G4","G6","T1","T10","T11","T13","T14","T3","T5c","T8"],"single_turn":["COH","E1","E2","E3","F1","F4","G5","T12","T2","T4","T5e","T7"]}},"findings":[{"block_threshold":null,"blocking_enabled":null,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["P6"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["1 criterion line(s) bundle multiple deliverables with 'and' (split so each is independently verifiable)."],"finding":"Acceptance-criteria / definition-of-done quality issues.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f607dd457c67f9209","impact":0.4,"is_primary":null,"location":"","norm_id":"ned06ebc801a522e3","priority":0.4,"reason":null,"scenarios":[],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Split compound criteria, replace subjective terms with observable outcomes, and state how each is verified.","tier":"DET","validity":1.0,"verification":null},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add a runnable pre-downgrade verification step (e.g., a CLI subcommand or script) that confirms every creation-bearing CREATE event has a corresponding new-code SNAPSHOT containing `creation_channel`, and specify either a compactor-level guard or a documented feature-flag mechanism to enforce the compaction pause during the rollback window.","cohort":["T11"],"criteria":["T11"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["'for a full binary downgrade, document the three-state compiled_state matrix and require compaction/event retirement to pause unless new-code snapshots already contain the field'","'verify that every creation-bearing CREATE has a new-code SNAPSHOT containing the field'","No AC item, no tooling spec, and no compactor guard covers this precondition check","DATA LOSS RISK is explicitly named but the only mitigation is documentation and manual procedure"],"finding":"The plan identifies a DATA LOSS RISK on full binary downgrade (old compactor retires creation-bearing CREATE events without writing creation_channel into SNAPSHOT), and instructs operators to 'pause compaction/event retirement' or 'verify that every creation-bearing CREATE has a new-code SNAPSHOT containing the field' — but neither a runnable verification command nor an enforcement mechanism (e.g., a guard in the compactor, a CLI check, a pre-retirement assertion) is specified anywhere in the plan, leaving the irreversible data-loss path dependent entirely on manual operator discipline with no safety net.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f40ee0cbdefeff7ad","impact":0.33,"is_primary":null,"location":"Architecture Decisions (downgrade/rollback section) and Risks and Mitigations (Snapshot data loss)","norm_id":"n5e7154ad873d6230","priority":0.2888,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["An operator performs a full binary downgrade and either misses the documentation or misunderstands the precondition; the compactor runs against tickets that have creation-bearing CREATEs but no new-code SNAPSHOT, retires those events, and creation_channel is permanently lost with no recovery path.","A partially-upgraded fleet (some nodes on old binary, some on new) runs compaction concurrently; without a compactor-level guard, the old-binary nodes may race the new-binary nodes and compact tickets before new-code SNAPSHOTs exist."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Add an AC line such as: 'A `rebar admin verify-creation-channel-snapshots` command (or equivalent script) exits non-zero if any ticket has a creation-bearing CREATE event without a new-code SNAPSHOT containing creation_channel; operators must run this and receive exit 0 before retiring any events during a full binary downgrade.' Additionally, add a compactor-level assertion that skips event retirement for tickets whose compiled_state lacks creation_channel unless the binary is explicitly configured with --allow-legacy-compaction.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.875,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"low","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"medium","reversibility":"hard","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add `tests/interfaces/contracts/test_schema_outputs.py` to the regression guard proof commands in child e622-a596-3ceb-4f74 and child 568c-b44b-7e2b-4d87.","cohort":["G3","G4"],"criteria":["G3"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Parent AC6 proof: 'uv run pytest -q tests/interfaces/contracts/test_schema_ticket_state.py tests/interfaces/contracts/test_schema_outputs.py tests/interfaces/io/test_export_ndjson.py && python -m rebar.schemas.gen_types --check'","Child 6fe2 AC5 includes test_schema_outputs.py as a primary proof target.","Child e622's full AC list: test_creation_channel.py, test_export_ndjson.py, test_import_idempotency.py, test_import_ndjson.py, test_inbound_leaf_bodies.py, test_env_aliasing.py, test_schema_coverage.py — no test_schema_outputs.py.","Child 568c's full AC list: test_creation_channel_compaction.py, test_reducer_snapshot.py, test_concurrency_regression.py, test_compact_rollback_recovery.py, test_fsck_snapshot_checks.py, test_event_schema_forward_compat.py, test_schema_coverage.py — no test_schema_outputs.py.","E622 adds creation_channel to NDJSON export output (AC4); 568c changes compiled_state shape seen through show/list/search. Both can affect schema output contract without test_schema_outputs.py catching regressions within their ACs.","container pairing: parent + 568c-b44b-7e2b-4d87/6fe2-ab22-c231-4a41/e622-a596-3ceb-4f74"],"finding":"test_schema_outputs.py is absent from e622 and 568c regression guards, leaving schema output contract breakage uncaught within those children.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f32a7625b9f5a38bf","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"child e622-a596-3ceb-4f74 AC4 / child 568c-b44b-7e2b-4d87 AC1","norm_id":"n349c924b778992f4","priority":0.0,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["E622 adds creation_channel to exported NDJSON via TicketState; if it inadvertently alters the TicketState schema shape in a way that breaks test_schema_outputs.py, no e622 AC will catch it — the regression only surfaces when the parent AC6 proof is run.","568c changes compiled_state projection after SNAPSHOT restore; if the resulting TicketState shape diverges from what test_schema_outputs.py asserts, no 568c AC will catch it."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"In e622's AC8 (or a new AC), append `tests/interfaces/contracts/test_schema_outputs.py` to the schema/lint proof. In 568c's AC6, include `tests/interfaces/contracts/test_schema_outputs.py` alongside the existing regression suite.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.625,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"module","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["T11"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":[],"finding":"During a rollback window, if the old compactor performs the FIRST compaction of new-code CREATE events (which carry `creation_channel` in the event payload), it will build a `compiled_state` SNAPSHOT without `creation_channel`. Once those CREATE events are retired, the recorded channel value is irrecoverably lost. The plan's 'older compactor carries creation_channel forward verbatim' guarantee only applies when creation_channel is ALREADY in `compiled_state` (i.e., a new-code SNAPSHOT already exists) — it does not protect against the first-compaction gap during rollback.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fa692d14e5835e09e","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Architecture Decisions — rollback paragraph: 'The operational back-out disables or reverts new writers while retaining the reader projection…' and 'the older compactor carries creation_channel forward even though its output schema does not expose it'","norm_id":"nc5282c03b8f69696","priority":0.0,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":[],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Add a precondition to the rollback runbook: creation-bearing CREATE events must not be retired before at least one successful new-code compaction has stored `creation_channel` in `compiled_state`. Alternatively, document the bounded loss window and add an AC that the rollback runbook states this explicitly.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.6875,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"na","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"insufficient","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"insufficient","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"insufficient"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"medium","reversibility":"hard","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add an AC (or extend an existing one) that explicitly proves the LEGACY_JIRA_AUTHOR/LEGACY_JIRA_ENV_ID constants are importable from rebar.reducer._version and that inbound_translate uses that exact import path — e.g., reference a test such as tests/unit/reducer/test_legacy_constants_import.py in the proof command for AC #5 or a new dedicated AC.","cohort":["COH","E1"],"criteria":["E1"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["'This does not depend on sibling reconciler package context and is pinned by an isolated spec-load contract test.' — Architecture Decisions","No AC references a test file such as tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/inbound_translate/test_constants_import.py or equivalent","AC #5 (-k legacy) tests inference behavior, not the import-path contract itself"],"finding":"The Architecture Decisions section explicitly names 'an isolated spec-load contract test' to pin the LEGACY_JIRA_AUTHOR/LEGACY_JIRA_ENV_ID absolute import contract (from rebar.reducer._version), but no Acceptance Criterion references a test file or proof command for this contract test, leaving it an uncovered described deliverable.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f01813ff264cd99ad","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Architecture Decisions (paragraph: 'inbound_translate._event_meta uses an absolute package import... pinned by an isolated spec-load contract test') vs Acceptance Criteria (no AC covers this)","norm_id":"n439611d29e20525d","priority":0.0,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":["If the import path drifts (e.g., constants moved to a different module), the inference will silently break with no failing AC to catch it","A reviewer or implementer cannot determine which child story is responsible for writing this contract test"],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Extend AC #5's proof command to include: `&& uv run pytest -q tests/unit/reducer/test_legacy_constants_import.py`, and add a one-line test that does `from rebar.reducer._version import LEGACY_JIRA_AUTHOR, LEGACY_JIRA_ENV_ID` and asserts their literal values.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.125,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"no","respects_artifact_altitude":"no","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Move (or cross-reference) the full-downgrade three-state schema matrix and compaction-retirement pause/precondition to a dedicated operator guide (e.g., docs/operations.md or docs/runbooks/downgrade.md) and update the AC proof command accordingly, or justify why docs/concurrency.md is the canonical operator-facing location.","cohort":["T4","T7"],"criteria":["T7"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["'docs/concurrency.md define CREATE/SNAPSHOT placement, the enum, Jira inference, import semantics … and the full-downgrade three-state schema matrix with its compaction-retirement pause/precondition'","Concurrency docs conventionally cover concurrent-write/read semantics, not operator downgrade procedures; the matrix and compaction-pause precondition are operational runbook content."],"finding":"The three-state compiled-state schema matrix and compaction-retirement pause/precondition — operator-facing downgrade procedures — are specified to live in docs/concurrency.md, which is a non-obvious location for rollback/deployment guidance and risks operators missing it when executing a downgrade.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f22c01776f6240ec1","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"AC — final bullet: 'docs/event-schema.md, docs/output-schemas.md, plus docs/concurrency.md define … the full-downgrade three-state schema matrix with its compaction-retirement pause/precondition.'","norm_id":"ne399027356ba7e28","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["An operator planning a downgrade consults docs/operations.md or a runbook, does not find the three-state matrix, proceeds without pausing compaction, and incurs irreversible creation_channel data loss on tickets not yet covered by new-code SNAPSHOTs."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.1429,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"no","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add an ADR or CLAUDE.md entry capturing the creation-channel provenance design decisions: closed vocabulary rationale, why the three-signal Jira predicate was chosen, what alternatives were rejected (call-stack inspection, mutable tags, actor/env redesign), and the supported back-out contract.","cohort":["T2","T5e"],"criteria":["T5e"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["AC requires updates to docs/event-schema.md, docs/output-schemas.md, and docs/concurrency.md — these cover the WHAT (schema placement, enum, inference, import semantics, downgrade matrix) but not the architectural WHY in a durable ADR form.","The plan body explains why call-stack inspection, mutable tags, and actor/environment redesign were rejected — this reasoning is not directed to any repo-resident decision record.","T5e criterion: 'A novel architectural decision is captured in an ADR / CLAUDE.md / design-doc update.'"],"finding":"The plan introduces a novel architectural decision (immutable creation-channel provenance, the three-signal legacy inference predicate, additive CREATE metadata contract, and rollback/downgrade matrix) but does not call for an ADR or CLAUDE.md update to durably capture the decision rationale alongside the code.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f6554124bac68a630","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Architecture Decisions section; Acceptance Criteria (docs bullet)","norm_id":"n06c2668865b966ac","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["A future engineer extending the closed vocabulary (e.g., adding a github channel) has no ADR to consult about why the vocabulary is closed and non-configurable, or why legacy inference is limited to Jira only.","A reviewer of the three-signal predicate has no durable record of why exactly those three signals were chosen and why near-misses must project unknown."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Add a docs/adr/NNN-creation-channel-provenance.md (or a CLAUDE.md section) that records: (1) the closed-vocabulary decision and extension protocol, (2) the three-signal legacy Jira inference rationale and false-positive controls, (3) alternatives considered and rejected, and (4) the downgrade/compaction risk matrix. Reference it from the AC documentation check.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.1429,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"na","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"no","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Define the concrete mechanism for the 'supported back-out' (e.g., a specific pinned binary version that has reader+compactor but no writer, or an env-var writer guard), and add a corresponding rollback test or runbook step so the path is verifiable.","cohort":["E3","T12"],"criteria":["T12"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["'No configuration switch or free-form channel extension is added.'","'The supported operational back-out disables new writers while retaining the new reader, schema, and compactor.'","ABSENCE: No intermediate binary, pinned version artifact, or writer-only feature flag is described that would mechanically implement this back-out."],"finding":"The 'supported operational back-out disables new writers' mechanism is unspecified: since the plan explicitly prohibits a configuration switch, there is no documented concrete path (intermediate binary version, build artifact, or deployment procedure) by which operators can disable creation_channel writes while retaining the new reader and compactor.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fcf4be82f9fd90b76","impact":0.264,"is_primary":null,"location":"Architecture Decisions — 'The supported operational back-out disables new writers while retaining the new reader, schema, and compactor.'","norm_id":"ned64c53b2f0c9139","priority":0.1173,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["An operator discovers a bug in channel attribution shortly after rollout and wants to stop recording bad creation_channel values; without a flag or documented intermediate binary, they have no tested cheap path — the only option is a full downgrade, which the plan labels as carrying DATA LOSS RISK."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Add a thin writer guard — even a single boolean compile-time constant or env-var escape hatch (e.g., REBAR_CREATION_CHANNEL_WRITE=0 defaults to 1) — so operators can disable new writes without a full downgrade. Document the pinned artifact or env-var in the operator guidance section alongside the compaction-pause precondition. If a flag is intentionally out-of-scope, replace 'supported operational back-out disables new writers' with an honest statement that the only back-out is the full-downgrade path and reference its data-loss matrix explicitly.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.4444,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"yes","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"no","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"low","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"moderate","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Consider whether create_core should require the channel parameter without a default (i.e., make it truly positional or keyword-only with no fallback) for internal callers, providing the 'python' default only at the public library facade boundary (create_ticket, idea, etc.) rather than inside the shared core — this would make omission a type/runtime error rather than a silent mis-attribution.","cohort":["G6"],"criteria":["G6"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan: 'New writes always record a concrete non-unknown value.'","Plan: 'Direct public Python calls default to python.'","Plan mitigation: 'enumerate every create_core and direct CREATE writer call site and pin each public facade/helper with a behavioral test' — this is purely test-time, not write-time enforcement.","Codebase: create_core currently has no channel parameter; after the feature, a caller omitting it gets 'python' silently rather than a validation error, because the parameter has a default."],"finding":"The plan's validation gate at create_core ('new local writers reject unknown or values outside the closed enum') is test-coverage-enforced rather than type-enforced: because the channel parameter defaults to 'python', any future internal call site added to the codebase that omits the channel will silently attribute 'python' rather than triggering a validation error. The plan's 'missed producer path' mitigation relies entirely on an enumeration test, which is correct for the declared scope but leaves no static or runtime backstop for net-new code paths introduced after the feature lands.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f47493882327b2229","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Architecture Decisions (paragraph: 'Every live producer declares its channel at its entry boundary') and Risks and Mitigations ('Missed producer path: enumerate every create_core and direct CREATE writer call site')","norm_id":"n9ed161d3645f314d","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["A future engineer adds a new internal creation helper that calls create_core directly without passing creation_channel — it silently reports 'python' even if it is, say, an import path or a Jira path.","A refactor moves a Jira inbound call through a helper layer that forgets to thread the 'jira' channel value — the ticket is silently misattributed as 'python' with no validation failure."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"At the public facade layer (rebar.create_ticket, rebar.idea, etc.) supply creation_channel='python' as an explicit argument when calling create_core, and make create_core's channel parameter keyword-only with NO default (required). This way any new call site that forgets the channel gets an immediate TypeError rather than silent misattribution. The plan's existing boundary threading approach is fully preserved; only the default placement changes.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.375,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Verify and document in the plan that the `from rebar.reducer._version import LEGACY_JIRA_AUTHOR, LEGACY_JIRA_ENV_ID` import in `inbound_translate` is placed **inside the function body** of `_event_meta` (following the established `_write_event_file` late-import pattern), not at module level, and explicitly call this out as the required pattern in the child ticket e622 implementation notes to prevent a module-level placement that would break spec-loaded isolation.","cohort":["T1"],"criteria":["T1"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan asserts: 'This does not depend on sibling reconciler package context and is pinned by an isolated spec-load contract test.'","inbound_translate.py module docstring for `_rebar_env`: 'Local to this module (each reconciler module keeps its own copy): the reconciler modules are spec-loaded under test where a cross-module import of a shared shim would not resolve.'","However, inbound_translate.py's `_write_event_file` already successfully uses `from rebar._store import event_append`, `from rebar._store import hlc`, `from rebar._commands import _seam` as LATE IMPORTS inside the function body — proving rebar.* package imports work when placed inside function bodies rather than at module level.","The plan does not specify whether the new import will be at module level (as a constant) or inside `_event_meta`'s function body — a critical distinction for spec-loaded test harness compatibility."],"finding":"The plan asserts that `from rebar.reducer._version import LEGACY_JIRA_AUTHOR, LEGACY_JIRA_ENV_ID` will resolve correctly within `inbound_translate._event_meta` under the isolated spec-loader test harness, but does not specify whether the import is placed at module level or inside the function body — and the existing `_rebar_env` module-level docstring explicitly warns that 'the reconciler modules are spec-loaded under test where a cross-module import of a shared shim would not resolve,' making this a placement-sensitive unverified capability assertion.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f418e56f4f3e1b1ff","impact":0.264,"is_primary":null,"location":"Architecture Decisions section: 'inbound_translate._event_meta uses an absolute package import (from rebar.reducer._version import LEGACY_JIRA_AUTHOR, LEGACY_JIRA_ENV_ID) for its defaults'; also child ticket e622-a596-3ceb-4f74 'Files' section: 'src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/inbound_translate.py: shared exact legacy Jira constants used through an absolute package import'","norm_id":"n508fd1a8eef0ec76","priority":0.099,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["An implementer places `LEGACY_JIRA_AUTHOR` and `LEGACY_JIRA_ENV_ID` as module-level constants imported from `rebar.reducer._version`, consistent with how other module-level constants in `inbound_translate.py` are defined. The isolated spec-loader test in `test_env_aliasing.py` then fails at module load time because the cross-package import cannot resolve, contradicting the plan's claim that it 'does not depend on sibling reconciler package context.'","The contract test ('extend the spec-load contract test') is written to verify the defaults but is placed after spec-loading, masking the module-level import failure until a CI run that exercises the full isolation path."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"In the Architecture Decisions section and child ticket e622's description, add: 'Place the import inside `_event_meta`'s function body as a late import (`from rebar.reducer._version import LEGACY_JIRA_AUTHOR, LEGACY_JIRA_ENV_ID`), following the same pattern as `_write_event_file`'s late `from rebar._store import ...` imports. Module-level placement will fail spec-loaded isolation. The contract test must load `inbound_translate` via the isolated spec-loader first, then assert both constants resolve to the expected literals.'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.375,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Explicitly specify the legacy projection helper's calling interface (parameter names and source) in e622's What section so that 568c can validate reusability before e622 merges.","cohort":["G3","G4"],"criteria":["G4"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":"novelty","evidence":["E622 What: 'Add one reducer helper for legacy channel projection … src/rebar/reducer/_processors.py: shared deterministic legacy projection helper.'","568c What: 'After process_snapshot restores compiled_state, run the same legacy projection helper used after CREATE only when creation_channel is absent.'","E622 Scope OUT: 'SNAPSHOT-only legacy inference, compaction.' This means e622 designs and tests the helper only in the full-log CREATE context.","568c Scope IN: 'post-SNAPSHOT legacy projection using the shared helper' — reuses e622's helper in a different invocation context (compiled_state after SNAPSHOT restore, not raw CREATE event data).","Neither child's ACs specify what parameters the helper accepts, leaving ambiguity about whether CREATE-event fields or compiled_state fields are its inputs.","container pairing: parent + 568c-b44b-7e2b-4d87/6fe2-ab22-c231-4a41/e622-a596-3ceb-4f74"],"finding":"The legacy projection helper interface defined in e622 (_processors.py) is implicitly required to be reusable in 568c's post-SNAPSHOT restore context, but neither child specifies the helper's calling signature, creating an unvalidated cross-child interface contract.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f692eeca47a20c8eb","impact":0.536,"is_primary":null,"location":"child e622-a596-3ceb-4f74 What/Files (src/rebar/reducer/_processors.py) → child 568c-b44b-7e2b-4d87 What (post-SNAPSHOT legacy projection using the shared helper)","norm_id":"nb67f24a015b206b6","priority":0.335,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["E622 implements the helper as `def infer_legacy_channel(event_data: dict)` taking raw CREATE event keys; 568c must call it with compiled_state fields after SNAPSHOT restore. If those field names differ (e.g., CREATE has 'author' vs. compiled_state has 'creator_author'), 568c must modify the helper or add an adapter — a scope creep discovered only at 568c implementation time.","E622's negative tests (legacy_negative) are written around CREATE event inputs; if the helper is later called from 568c with compiled_state inputs, the negative test coverage may not transfer, leaving false-positive inference risks in the SNAPSHOT path undetected."],"severity":"major","suggested_fix":"In e622's What section, specify the helper signature — e.g., `def infer_legacy_channel(ticket_id: str, author: str | None, env_id: str | None) -> dict` — using field names that are present in both raw CREATE.data and post-SNAPSHOT compiled_state. Add a note in 568c's What section confirming which compiled_state fields map to those parameters.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.625,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"module","debt_impact":"medium","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"moderate","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"medium"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Specify the concrete mechanism for disabling new creation_channel writers during the supported back-out (e.g., deploy a pinned intermediate binary that omits the writer changes, a deployment-manifest flag, or an explicit binary version boundary) so the back-out is executable without a config switch.","cohort":["T4","T7"],"criteria":["T4"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":"novelty","evidence":["'No configuration switch or free-form channel extension is added.'","'The supported operational back-out disables new writers while retaining the new reader, schema, and compactor.'","No mechanism (intermediate binary, deployment toggle, env var, etc.) is named for the back-out write-disable step."],"finding":"The plan states 'No configuration switch is added' yet also states 'The supported operational back-out disables new writers while retaining the new reader, schema, and compactor' — the mechanism by which operators disable new writers without a config switch is never specified, leaving the back-out plan non-executable.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f4e468bad1817acd4","impact":0.264,"is_primary":null,"location":"Architecture Decisions — rollback paragraph; Risks and Mitigations — 'Compatibility' bullet","norm_id":"na2ae28f2e5630e23","priority":0.132,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["An operator needs to roll back after discovering a bug in channel attribution; they know they should disable new writes but have no documented mechanism to do so, forcing improvised action or a full binary downgrade that incurs the acknowledged DATA LOSS RISK."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Add a sentence such as: 'The supported back-out deploys the last binary revision before this feature (tag vX.Y.Z-pre-channel) which omits writer changes but is forward-compatible with the new reader/schema/compactor; no application-level flag is needed.'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.5,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"low","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"moderate","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}}],"impact_model_version":"plan-v3","material_fingerprint":"fdbea9511b9f9157","metrics":{"claim_path":"no-llm/no-network (structural; the fast claim check is a local HMAC verify)","det_ms":257.5,"llm_calls":23,"llm_ms":728350.2,"total_ms":728741.6,"verify_requests":34},"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","regver":"b293b9a55de591cc","runner":"pydantic_ai","schema":"plan_review_result_v2","ticket_id":"jira-reb-977","ticket_type":"epic","verdict":"PASS","verified_at_sha":"cb0f8ec3b0641860ea6139431ccc63ca528c4732"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"REVIEW_RESULT","timestamp":1784262772338330001,"uuid":"854a4924-8a55-4c38-a240-04bf899920fd"}